---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/PageHeader.astro";
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Rules"
  description="The Under 12s (15-a-side) contact rugby rules the Rhiwbina Squirrels play under, plus what changes from U11 to U12."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="Under 12s · 15-a-side contact"
    title="Rules"
    lead="At U12 the Squirrels play the full 15-a-side game — including the set piece. Here's how it works, and what's changed from U11."
  />
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-narrow flow">
      <Card title="At a glance">
        <dl class="facts">
          <div>
            <dt>Age</dt>
            <dd>Under 12 as on 1 September at the start of the season</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Team size</dt>
            <dd>
              15 players — eight forwards max, seven backs max. Both teams field
              the same number throughout; a sent-off player is not replaced, so
              that team is a player down.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Periods of play</dt>
            <dd>Two halves of up to 25 minutes — maximum 50 minutes, no extra time</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Playing area</dt>
            <dd>A full-size field, up to 100m long × 70m wide</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Ball size</dt>
            <dd>Size four</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Coach</dt>
            <dd>UKCC Level 1 (Level 2 Coach Award recommended)</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Referee</dt>
            <dd>WRU Level 1 Award</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </Card>

      <Card title="How the game is played">
        <p>
          IRB Under 19 Laws apply, <strong>apart from</strong> the variations
          below.
        </p>
        <dl class="rules">
          <div>
            <dt>The team</dt>
            <dd>
              Eight forwards, seven backs, with rolling replacements. Players
              must leave and enter the field at the halfway touchline. Full IRB
              laws apply at the contact area.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Scrums</dt>
            <dd>
              Crouch, touch, pause, engage. An eight-player
              <strong>contested</strong> scrum with a maximum 0.5m push and no
              wheeling. Both hookers may strike for the ball. Both packs must use
              a 3-4-1 formation, and the number 8 may pick the ball up from the
              base.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Scrum half</dt>
            <dd>The offside line at a scrum is the mid line of the scrum.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Lineout</dt>
            <dd>
              A full lineout, uncontested, with no catch and drive. The
              non-scoring team restarts with a drop kick.
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Kicking</dt>
            <dd>Kicking is allowed anywhere on the field.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Penalties &amp; free kicks</dt>
            <dd>
              The ball must be propelled from the hands. A kick at goal is only
              allowed for offences committed inside the 22-metre area. For a
              quick free kick or penalty, place the ball on the ground and tap it
              forward with the foot — correct technique must be used to restart.
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </Card>

      <Card title="What's new at U12 (changes from U11)">
        <p>
          Moving up from U11? These are the main differences now that the full
          game is introduced.
        </p>
        <dl class="changes">
          <div>
            <dt>Team size</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: up to 12 (max 5 forwards)</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to">U12: 15 (max 8 forwards)</span>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Periods of play</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: 20 min each way (max 40)</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to">U12: two halves up to 25 min (max 50)</span>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Playing area</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: 22m lines, 5m in from touch</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to">U12: full-size field (100m × 70m)</span>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Ball size</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: size three</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to">U12: size four</span>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Scrums</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from"
                >U11: passive (no push/wheel), 5 forwards 3:2, scrum member can't
                pick up</span
              >
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to"
                >U12: contested (0.5m max push), 8 forwards 3-4-1, no. 8 can pick
                up</span
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Lineout</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: four-man, uncontested</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to">U12: full lineout, uncontested</span>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Kicking</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: drop-kick restart, own half only</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to">U12: kicking allowed anywhere</span>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Hand-off / fend-off</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: not allowed (free kick)</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to">U12: full IRB contact-area laws apply</span>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Breakdown</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: one player per team contests, no maul</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to">U12: full IRB contact-area laws</span>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>Penalties</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: all penalties are free kicks (tap with foot)</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to"
                >U12: ball from the hands, kick at goal allowed in the 22</span
              >
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt>What it introduces</dt>
            <dd>
              <span class="from">U11: the contest for possession at the breakdown</span>
              <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
              <span class="to">U12: the full game and the set piece</span>
            </dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
        <p class="muted">
          A quick summary for parents — for the full detail, see the WRU
          age-grade rugby laws.
        </p>
      </Card>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .facts,
  .rules,
  .changes {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-s);
  }
  .facts div,
  .rules div {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(8rem, auto) 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-2xs) var(--space-s);
  }
  .facts dt,
  .rules dt,
  .changes dt {
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .facts dd,
  .rules dd,
  .changes dd {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .changes div {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-3xs);
  }
  .changes dd {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--space-3xs) var(--space-2xs);
  }
  .changes .from {
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }
  .changes .to {
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .changes .arrow {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .muted {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }

  @media (max-width: 30rem) {
    .facts div,
    .rules div {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-3xs);
    }
  }
</style>
